What Its Made of You know we're all about being atmosphere responsible, but we're also people friendly too. That's why everything down to the coating on our bamboo is non-toxic. At the Core Our products use less energy and emit fewer greenhouse gases in production. By choosing products made from plant based materials, which break down safely and quickly, you've made a responsible choice for you and the planet.

Product Elements All Full Circle products are made without harmful coatings, dyes, plastics and chemicals to make sure your family gets a healthier clean. We design many of our products with parts you can replace once they’re looking a little less than fresh, extending the life cycle, saving resources and money. From composting to nixing plastic water bottles, you make all the right choices for a more conscientious lifestyle. Our products just help make it a bit easier to tackle every day. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2016
reviews.reviewText: I bought this broom and dust pan soley because I like the way it looked! I did find that Amazon had a better price than the stores when I purchased it as well. It functions pretty well, I like that the dust pan has a nice easy lip to scoop up debris with, and it's deep and can hold a decent amount of dust. The only thing I've noticed is that it's a little hard to get nooks and crannies and sharp edges, specifically when I'm sweeping the stairs. There is a bit of a lip on the ends of the brush that hits the wall before the bristles do. No biggie, I just have to do a couple extra sweeps when I'm dusting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Of diamonds and dustpans
reviews.reviewText: OK, I feel a little bit depressed to be reviewing a dustpan. I would rather be reviewing a large, canary yellow diamond solitaire ring, for example. Nonetheless, I purchased the dustpan and not the ring, so here goes...Among brush and dustpan sets, this one is a standout. The brush has fine, dense, flexible bristles that conform to every surface and sweep really well. The pan is deep, with a soft rubber lip, and its top edges curve over to contain the dust inside. Brush your crumbs into a pile, and with one stroke, sweep the pile into the pan. No need to chase around that line of crumbs that usually remains by the lip of the dustpan - you know the one I mean.When you are done cleaning up, the bamboo brush fits into the handle of the dustpan, making a tidy and attractive package. It looks like it was designed with care - not mass-produced.Overall, it is the large, canary yellow diamond solitaire of dustpans.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2015
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute set - ideal for college (instructions included in review)
reviews.reviewText: What a lovely dustpan and brush set. Made from sustainable bamboo and recycle plastic, who could ask for more!This didn't come with instructions so, for the benefit of those new to college life, I will supply mine, learned through much trial and error:(1) Remove brush by pulling out from convenient holder in handle.(2) Place dustpan (the flat bit) in front of the dust/dirt/small objects you want to pick up (Note: items should be dry for best results)(3) Hold handle of pan and tilt slightly(4) Now, holding the brush in your other hand by the handle place it on the far side of the dirt to be collected, bristle side down (this is important)(5) The arrangement should be pan - dirt - brush (bristles DOWN)(6) Apply just sufficient pressure to press the bristles slightly against the floor but still to allow you to draw the brush towards the dirt and the pan in one "sweeping" motion(7) Dirt should be "swept" into the pan(8) Carefully lift pan with dirt. Important tip: keep it horizontal (if you forget this simply go back to step 2, above)(9) Go to trash can and tilt the pan so that (most of) the dirt falls into can(10) Place brush back into handy holder.Congratulations, you've swept up something.
